 East London - The Transnet Phelophepha healthcare train is in the Buffalo City Metro this week. "The train is stationed at the Mount Ruth train station near Mdantsane and is offering various health services at no cost until Friday," the Metro said. "Amongst the services on offer is the screening and testing for the coronavirus. "Residents especially those who feel virus-related symptoms are advised and encouraged to take advantage of this and visit the train." Do not forget to wear your mask, keep distance from each other and practice hygiene. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 